# Multi-Model Routing (Cursor)

This project uses Claude Code as orchestrator with Gemini and Codex subagents.

## Routing
- Large analysis (10+ files) → delegate to Gemini CLI
- Focused bug fix (1-5 files) → delegate to Codex CLI  
- Batch/docs → Gemini Flash
- Architecture/complex reasoning → Claude stays here

## CLI quick refs
```bash
gemini -m gemini-2.5-flash --all-files -p "PROMPT"
codex exec --full-auto "TASK"
```

See CLAUDE.md for full routing matrix.

## Dashboard (dashboard/)

This is a Next.js 15 app with the following conventions:

- Streaming: all AI responses use `AsyncGenerator<string>` via `lib/stream.ts`
- SSE: `/api/chat/route.ts` emits `routing | token | done | error` events — do not change event names
- Agent routing: keyword rules live in `lib/agents.ts` ROUTING_RULES array
- Never add blocking awaits inside the SSE ReadableStream controller
- Model IDs in `AGENTS` must match provider-accepted IDs exactly
- Run `npm test` before any push — smoke tests must pass
